{"parse":{"title":"Academic specialization","pageid":21490880,"revid":819661539,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Academia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Academia\">academia</a>, <b>specialization</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/American_and_British_English_spelling_differences#-ise.2C_-ize_.28-isation.2C_-ization.29\" title=\"American and British English spelling differences\">or</a> <b>specialisation</b>) may be a course of study or <a href=\"/wiki/Academic_major\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Academic major\">major</a> at an academic institution or may refer to the field that a <a href=\"/wiki/Specialist_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"Specialist (disambiguation)\">specialist</a> practices in.\n</p><p>As the volume of knowledge accumulated by humanity became too great, increasing specialization in academia appeared in response.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Academic_specialization&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation web\">Crichton, Danny. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.stanforddaily.com/2010/02/18/adventures-in-academia-the-dangers-of-overspecialization/\">\"Adventures in Academia: The Dangers of (Over)Specialization\"</a>. <i>Stanford Daily</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-03-04</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Stanford+Daily&amp;rft.atitle=Adventures+in+Academia%3A+The+Dangers+of+%28Over%29Specialization&amp;rft.aulast=Crichton&amp;rft.aufirs